pageContext.claim: “Remember, Hillary? She came up with a phrase; it was a disaster. They paid millions, then she had to change it one day into the campaign because I attacked it. I said -- remember, I said, ‘See it's all about her.’ They changed it. They paid a guy millions of dollars. He walked away -- retired.”
pageContext.analysis: This is totally false. A graphic designer (who has not retired) came up with the slogan "I'm With Her" for a bumper-sticker contest. As the campaign progressed, Hillary Clinton adopted a different slogan: "Stronger Together."
